cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NI 

This paper is primarily focused on evaluating and comparing visual representations in both neural systems and machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks and deep learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a new benchmark for evaluating visual representations, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it involves the development of a new evaluation method.
